      • size

        public int size()
        Size method of type int that returns the size of the array stack, the number of cells in the array that are occupied by elements, through the count variable.
        Specified by:
        size in interface MinimalStackADT<T>

      • push

        public void push(T element)
        Pushes an element to the circular array stack. The top pointer is set to the current element, then incremented to point to the next empty space in the array stack. The count is also incremented to hold the current number of elements in the array. However, if the size of the array stack is same as the length when the push method is called, then a method to double the capacity of the array stack is called.
        Specified by:
        push in interface MinimalStackADT<T>

      • pop

        public T pop()
        Pops an element from the top of the stack, stores the popped element in a temporary variable and returns that element. The top pointer and the counter for the size method is also decremented. Throws an IllegalStateException if the method is called on a stack that contains no elements.
        Specified by:
        pop in interface MinimalStackADT<T>

      • peek

        public T peek()
        Peeks at the top element in the stack and returns it. Throws an IllegalStateException if the method is called on a stack that contains no elements.
        Specified by:
        peek in interface MinimalStackADT<T>

      • isEmpty

        public boolean isEmpty()
        Boolean method that checks the count by calling the size() method, returning true if it is 0 and returning false if it is not 0.
